visited stephanie at her dorm as she was preparing for her presentation. i tried to make one too and at first encountered failure. the penny looked like a mangle tool whit pieces of it sticking upward. it resembled a small pinwheel. then i figured out a trick by using the back edges of the cutco scissors the penny buckled, twisted and i formed it to look like a corkscrew. this left stephanie enthusiastically happy and i showed her my trick to making it. she then asked me to help me with her presentation. dot was just smiling. we took the
train to our friend peter's apartment who was stephanie's appointment for the night. when we got there, stephanie did her schtik and won peter over with her presentation. i gave an impromtu show with the penny cutting and when the show was over. peter was ready to buy the big knife for his kitchen. he gave stephanie some constructive criticism about her presentation. steph took it positively. we were so glad that she was handling herself professionally that dot and i gave her some referrals. dot's other cousin kathy arrived later for the show. she was a little more light
